data.content:
## Breaking Changes: OpenAPI.NET v1 → v2

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. Here are the issues in your code and fixes:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed
Schema examples now use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode`:

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` no longer extends `Dictionary`
It no longer implements `IDictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`. Use the `Schemes` property:

```csharp
// Before
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new()
    {
        Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
        {
            [oAuthScheme] = scopes
        }
    }
};
```

### 3. `schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses a type-based nullability model via the `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;

// (To make something nullable, you'd do:)
// property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

### 4. `ReferenceType` → constructor change
`OpenApiReference` now takes the id/type via its constructor:

```csharp
// Before
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }

// After
Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2", ReferenceType.SecurityScheme)
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2", ReferenceType.SecurityScheme)
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

The `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` directive can be removed entirely — that namespace no longer exists in v2.
